Back in December, I managed to get a poem accepted into Amaze: The Cinquain Journal. Amaze is an online publication, but it also produces an annual printed compilation. This compilation is finally out and can be purchased here. My poem entitled "Sunbathing Lovers" can be found in the Summer section. I highly recommend buying yourself a copy.

1. Go to your profile and make sure you have 25 or more interests.
2. Comment on this post. (One comment per person, please!)
3. I will go to your profile and choose one* of your interests to make an icon about and make an icon.
4. I will then compile and post an entry with all the icons made during the interest meme.

* = I may get inspired and make more than one icon from your interests, or more than one icon from one interest - say, three icons about cats.

If you read this, please consider boycotting this year's Olympics. A message needs to be sent to Communist China that their complete disregard for human rights should not be tolerated. Please, think about the dangerous pollution, censorship, torture, murder, forced abortions, organ harvesting, religious persecution, genocide, kidnapping, child labor, etc. This is everyone's problem. We can't condone this. We have to stand up and say "This is wrong!" and do something, instead of ignoring the issues just so we can watch some sporting events on TV.

Epitaph for a Darling Lady All her hours were yellow sands, Blown in foolish whorls and tassels; Slipping warmly through her hands; Patted into little castles. Shiny day on shiny day Tumbled in a rainbow clutter, As she flipped them all away, Sent them spinning down the gutter. Leave for her a red young rose, Go your way, and save your pity; She is happy, for she knows That her dust is very pretty. -- Dorothy Parker :) And I'd prefer to have an urn.

It's certianly not perfect, but here's a calendar of Buddhist holidays/observances that I ganked from a few different sites and then modified. Most of the observances are Tibetan, but there are also the big three Zen days (Buddha's birth, enlightenment, and death) because I like to celebrate those things outside of Vesak, and then there are a few days relating to Kuan Shih Yin because I have a love and respect for her as another embodiment of Chenrezig/Tara. I know, I know. I'm such a Salad Bar Buddhist. There are a number of things not included, I know, such as auspicious days, prayer flag days, moons, certain pujas, etc. If there is anyone on my f-list (looooong shot here) that knows anything about the Tibetan Calendar, and knows that I've missed something BIG (are there more days for the Medicine Buddha or Chenrezig, or more Sojong Days, for example?) then feel free to let me know. It feels a little bit incomplete. Anyway, onto the calendar! * 1/22: Amitabha Buddha Day * 2/5: Sojong Day (Tibetan Buddhist day of fasting, confession, and reparation for harm done) * 2/6: Shakyamuni Buddha Day * 2/7 to 2/21: Losar (Tibetan Buddhist New Year) * 2/14: Tara Puja * 2/15: Nirvana Day * 2/21: Amitabha Buddha Day * 3/7: Shakyamuni Buddha Day * 3/15: Tara Puja * 3/21: Amitabha Buddha Day * 3/26: Kuan Yin's Birthday * 4/6: Shakyamuni Buddha Day * 4/8: Buddha's Birthday * 4/13: Day for meditation on Avalokitesvara and Green Tara * 4/20: Amitabha Buddha Day * 5/5: Shakyamuni Buddha Day * 5/12: Tara Puja * 5/19 Vesak (Tibetan celebration of Buddha's Birth, Enlightenment, and Death) * 5/19: Amitabha Buddha Day * 6/3: Shakyamuni Buddha Day * 6/11: Tara Puja * 6/18: Amitabha Buddha Day * 7/3: Shakyamuni Buddha Day * 7/6: Celebration of Buddha's first Teaching * 7/6: H.H. The Dalai Lama's Birthday * 7/10: Tara Puja * 7/18: Amitabha Buddha Day * 8/1: Shakyamuni Buddha Day * 8/9: Tara Puja * 8/16: Amitabha Buddha Day * 8/30: Shakyamuni Buddha Day * 9/7: Day for meditation on Gold Tara (provider of all sustenance and necessities) * 9/15: Amitabha Buddha Day * 9/29: Shakyamuni Buddha Day * 10/7: Tara Puja * 10/14: Amitabha Buddha Day * 10/17: Celebration of Kuan Yin's attainment of Bodhisattvahood * 10/21: Lha Bab Duchen (Tibetan Buddhists celebrate the Buddha's descent from heaven after teaching the Dharma there) * 10/28: Shakyamuni Buddha Day * 11/6: Day for meditation on White Tara * 11/13: Amitabha Buddha Day * 11/22: Day for meditation on Manjusri and Prajna-Paramita * 11/27: Shakyamuni Buddha Day * 12/5: Day for meditation on Red Tara (protector against evil and harm) * 12/8: Bodhi Day * 12/12: Amitabha Buddha Day * 12/27: Shakyamuni Buddha Day

Another rejection today. (They're pouring in now, aren't they?) This one is from The Threepenny Review. Small ouch. I'm still holding out for The Paris Review, but it could be a silly dream. I'll send some more work out to some new magazines in the beginning of next month. I should hang out with David this weekend, but I really don't feel like it. I really don't feel very sociable right now.

It's funny that I just went into a poetry update yesterday, and today I recieved another rejection. This one was from Poetry. Oh well, that particular submission was not some of my best work. I also just sent an online submission to The New Yorker, on a silly whim. I'm going to be waiting awhile before any more submissions. I need to either get some of my better poetry back from the magazines or get to writing. I'm running out of (good) work! Here's a list of the poems that I currently have out: Agnes I Senga Begin Botticelli Baby Catch It In A Glass Dawning Dear Poet Faded Lovers First Time Free-Form Ganymede Her Lover Lady of Raffaello Santi Lovesick Lunch Melting Mielikki Missed Train Old Friends Orange Wood Our Time Pillows of Old Perfume Possessions Sacrament Sleeping Angel Song of Luna Maria Streetlights Sulfur The Countess The Way I Am Theatre d'Elsinore Tell Sylvie Trespass Two Runners Weeping Wind Wishing Well
with Myself. And maybe Meghan Murphy aka , the creator of the popular and ever-so-cute Kawaii Not comic. She drew this for me:

(I took my MUCH needed nap. I feel a little better now. I should update on what else has been going on in my life, but there is so much that I don't want to talk about still. Maybe I'll feel up to actually updating next week.) Right now, I'd like to do an update on my writing. So far, I have written 12 poems this year. I have submitted 8 poetry manuscripts to literary magazines. I have received 1 rejection (from The American Poetry Review), and I am still waiting for responses from the others. It has been 24 days since I sent my submission to The Paris Review. It has been 20 days since I sent my submissions to Poetry and The Threepenny Review. It's only been one day since I sent my submissions to The Sun, The Yale Review, and Folio. I also sent out a new submission to The American Poetry Review. I set up some tickers on iGoogle (<3) to help me keep track of my waiting periods. I have quite a long way to go. Click through to large screencap. I think I'm going to send out 4 submissions for every rejection I get and then some. I'm trying to get somewhat serious about this. Oh, I also am going to stop using Allpoetry.com so that I can focus more on getting published. So if you would like to read any of my poetry from now on, it would be best just to contact me and I will send you some. :)

Awhile back, I posted about a bunch of artwork that I had saved on Photobucket getting deleted for violating their terms of service. Now, this was work from Audrey Kawasaki. I had more of her art saved in the same album. A good amount of her work does deal with nudity and erotica, but nothing I posted was any worse than anything else I had seen hosted by Photobucket. I guess some nudity is more kosher than others? It seems unfair, but by agreeing to the Photobucket terms of service when I signed up, there's nothing I can do but bitch and moan about the whole thing. For giggles, I thought I'd try ImageShack (and see if they'll have any problems with them) and post the "unacceptable" pictures for anyone who might be interested in seeing them. Again, I've seen so much worse on Photobucket... so I'm still confused.

What Mental Disorder Are you?
Bipolar Disorder: You are Bipolar Disorder. With Bipolar Disorder comes very dramatic mood swings called episodes of mania or depression. With a mania episode, there's an increase of energy, an overly happy mood, extreme irritability, talking really fast, jumping from one thought to another, and an unability to concentrate. There's very little sleep needed, an unrealistic belief in one's own abilities and powers. Poor judgement and spending sprees arefrequent in a Manic Episode, same with an increased sex drive, abuse in drugs and alcohol, and agressiveness. Funnily enough, there's also a denail that anything is wrong.When in a Depressed Episode, you or a REAL bipolar person tend to be depressed all say every day until the episode is over. There's a noticable lack of interest or pleasure in anything during the episode. There's also significant weight loss or weight gain. Insomnia or hypersomnia every day, fatigue or loss of energy, excessive feelings of worthlessness, indecisiveness, and suicidalness. Medication will be good for you for the depression episodes.

THE RULES Pick 11 of your favorite movies. Then pick one of your favorite quotes from each movie. (NO GOOGLING!) Post the quotes in your journal. Have those on your friends list guess what the movie is. Either strike out the quote once it has been correctly identified or place the guesser's user name directly after the quote. Extra points for knowing the actor or character's name. 1. I chose nothing. I was born and this is what I am. 2. You know, sometimes I wish I did a little more with my life instead of hanging out in front of places selling weed and shit. Like, maybe be an animal doctor. Why not me? I like seals and shit. Or maybe an astronaut. Yeah... be the first motherfucker to see a new galaxy, or find a new alien lifeform... and fuck it. People would be like, "There he goes. Homeboy fucked a Martian once." coldwizard 3. I hope that when the world comes to an end, I can breathe a sigh of relief, because there will be so much to look forward to. 4. When I first came here, this was all swamp. Everyone said I was daft to build a castle on a swamp, but I built it all the same, just to show them. It sank into the swamp. So I built a second one. That sank into the swamp. So I built a third. That burned down, fell over, then sank into the swamp. But the fourth one stayed up. And that's what you're going to get, Lad, the strongest castle in all of England. smeebubbles 5. Strange, isn't it? Each man's life touches so many other lives. When he isn't around he leaves an awful hole, doesn't he? 6. Too many guys think I'm a concept, or I complete them, or I'm gonna make them alive. But I'm just a fucked-up girl who's lookin' for my own piece of mind; don't assign me yours. coldwizard 7. That song was by a young mister Kurt Cobain - now that kid's got a future! free_as_verse 8. It's a bridesmaid's dress. Someone loved it intensely for one day, and then tossed it. Like a Christmas tree. So special. Then, bam, it's on the side of the road. Tinsel still clinging to it. Like a sex crime victim. Underwear inside out. Bound with electrical tape. nzfriend 9. So it's sorta social, demented and sad, but social. 10. I tried to kill myself with a Lady Bic. A pink plastic razor with daisies on it and a moisturizing strip. smeebubbles 11. Janie's a pretty typical teenager. Angry, insecure, confused. I wish I could tell her that's all going to pass, but I don't want to lie to her.
